Do you want to download a version from a U.S. site, or do you want to
download a version that you can use in the U.S. without criminal or civil
repercussions?

If you are interested in the latter, I would suggest a site in Germany
that has a very complete collection of PGP versions back to 1.0, including
U.S. and international versions of the 2.6.x versions.  Happily, they
also carry OS/2 versions of these, which I believe were actually ported
by the person who maintains the collection.  (Thanks!)  For U.S. use
you would want to go to the 2.6.2 directory and get the OS/2 version.

Check it out at:
  ftp://ftp.informatik.uni-hamburg.de/pub/virus/crypt/pgp/

